The Durban police officer who was shot and critically injured in this morning’s shooting on Winter Road in Musgrave has died on in hospital. Rescue Care managing director, Garrith Jamieson, confirmed the policeman’s death. “I have just received confirmation that the policeman passed away in theatre. Condolences to the family,” said Jamieson. The vehicle used by the suspect in his getaway, was also recovered earlier on Barnett Road in Sydenham. The suspect remains at large and a police manhunt is underway.